CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 30, 1957, pg. 45 reads: " Penn Staters' Party - In spite of the fact that the University of Pittsburgh defeated their alma mater in a close football game Saturday, the loss didn't dampen the party spirit of loyal Penn State University followers (a majority of them Pittsburghers) who made the trip. Among the after-game soirees was the one hosted by Clarence Rogers Jr., seated, lower left, first row, at his parents' home, 821 Finland St., Schenley Heights, was a real-gone bash, and a good time was had by all.  The smiles testify to that, don't you think? - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of ten women, and fourteen men, including Clarence Rogers Jr., seated on floor, left, gathered in Rogers home, 821 Finland Street, Schenley Heights
